{"body": "<div id=\"doc-contents\" class=\"content\">\n\n  <h1>ScalingRule object</h1>\n  <p></p>\n\n\n    <h2>Abstract Type</h2>\n\n    <p><em>ScalingRule</em> is an abstract type. When an object of type <em>ScalingRule</em> is expected, you must pass an object of one of the following types:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"/definitions/B/BasicScalingRule.html\">BasicScalingRule</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/definitions/D/DateAndTimeScalingRule.html\">DateAndTimeScalingRule</a></li>\n    </ul>\n\n\n\n\n  <h2>Properties</h2>\n  <table class=\"fullwidth\">\n    <thead>\n      <tr>\n        <th>property</th>\n        <th>attributes</th>\n        <th>valid values</th>\n        <th>description</th>\n        <th>filter option</th>\n      </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <td><span class=\"fixed-width\">name</span><br/><span class=\"data-type\">\n            string\n        </span></td>\n        <td><span class=\"notes\">\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip required\">required</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip create-only\">create-only</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip filterable\">filterable</span><br>\n        </span></td>\n        <td>\n        </td>\n        <td></td>\n        <td>\n            ?name=...\n        </td>      \n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td><span class=\"fixed-width\">ruleType</span><br/><span class=\"data-type\">\n            string\n        </span></td>\n        <td><span class=\"notes\">\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip required\">required</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip create-only\">create-only</span><br>\n            <span class=\"need-tooltip filterable\">filterable</span><br>\n        </span></td>\n        <td>\n            \"BasicScalingRule\"<br/>\"LoadAveragesScalingRule\"<br/>\"FreeRamScalingRule\"<br/>\"UrlResponseTimeScalingRule\"<br/>\"SqsQueueSizeScalingRule\"<br/>\"DateAndTimeScalingRule\"<br/>\"BandWidthScalingRule\"\n        </td>\n        <td></td>\n        <td>\n            ?ruleType=...\n        </td>      \n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n\n  <h2>Endpoints using this object</h2>\n  <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"/user/farm-roles/scaling/post.html\">User / Farm Roles / Scaling: Create</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/user/farm-roles/scaling/get.html\">User / Farm Roles / Scaling: List</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/user/farm-roles/scaling/patch.html\">User / Farm Roles / Scaling: Edit</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/user/farm-roles/scaling/delete_metricName.html\">User / Farm Roles / Scaling: Delete</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/user/farm-roles/scaling/get_metricName.html\">User / Farm Roles / Scaling: Get</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/user/farm-roles/scaling/patch_metricName.html\">User / Farm Roles / Scaling: Edit</a></li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n$(function () {\n  var descriptions = {\n    \"required\": \"<i>Required</i> properties must be set when you send a <i>ScalingRule</i> object to the API.\",\n    \"optional\": \"You can choose wether or not to set <i>Optional</i> properties when sending <i>ScalingRule</i> objects to Scalr.\",\n    \"create-only\": \"<i>Create-only</i> properties are set when the object is created, but can't be modified later. They are typically allowed in POST requests but not in PATCH requests.\",\n    \"read-only\": \"<i>Read-only</i> properties are set by Scalr and can't be modified through the API. They are set when you retrieve a <i>ScalingRule</i> from Scalr, but you should not set them when sending <i>ScalingRule</i> objects to Scalr through POST or PATCH requests.\",\n    \"filterable\": \"<i>Filterable</i> properties can be used to filter the results returned by the API according to the value of these properties.\"\n  };\n  var spans = document.querySelectorAll('.need-tooltip');\n  for (var i = 0; i < spans.length; i ++) {\n    for (var cls in descriptions) {\n      var span = spans.item(i);\n      if ($(span).hasClass(cls)) {\n        new Tooltip({\n          target: span,\n          content: descriptions[cls],\n          classes: 'tooltip-theme-arrows',\n          position: 'top left'\n        });\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n});\n</script>\n", "title": "ScalingRule definition - Scalr API Documentation"}